[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1431[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1440[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1431[0m[39m:void [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1432[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1433[0m[39m:  struct doh_probes *doh = data->req.doh;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1434[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1435[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1436[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mcurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1437[0m[39m:    data->req.doh->req_hds = NULL;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1438[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1439[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1440[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash arises from a wild read in Curl_doh_close when it dereferences [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh` after that memory has already been freed.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `Curl_doh_cleanup`, the code calls `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, frees the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`doh_probes` struct via `[0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, but never resets [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh` to NULL.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A subsequent invocation of `Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor example, through additional [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcleanup calls or in multi-handle teardown[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m sees a non-NULL `data->req.doh` pointer,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdereferences it [0m[1;39m([0m[39myielding a use-after-free[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and triggers a wild-address read.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Strategy to Fix[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Modify `lib/doh.c` in the `Curl_doh_cleanup` function so that after freeing [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh`, the pointer is reset to NULL.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This ensures that any later calls to `Curl_doh_close` will early-exit when [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecking `[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi.e. `data->req.doh == NULL`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, preventing dereferencing freed [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemory.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes to harness code, tests, or external/fuzzing logic are required.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Steps to Implement the Patch[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m In `lib/doh.c`, locate the `Curl_doh_cleanup` function [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround lines [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1431[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m1440[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Refactor the cleanup block:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Use the local variable `doh` [0m[1;39m([0m[39malready assigned as `struct doh_probes *doh =[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata->req.doh;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to clear the header list.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - After calling `[0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, add `data->req.doh = NULL;`.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m The revised function should look like this:[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      void [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        struct doh_probes *doh = data->req.doh;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Close and remove any active DoH probe handles *[0m[35m/[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Free the headers list, then clear the field in the local struct *[0m[35m/[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mcurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          doh->req_hds = NULL;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Free the doh_probes struct and null out the pointer to avoid UAF *[0m[35m/[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          data->req.doh = NULL;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Rebuild and run the fuzzing suite to confirm the crash no longer occurs.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Resetting `data->req.doh` to NULL immediately after freeing prevents [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubsequent calls to `Curl_doh_close` from operating on freed memory, eliminating [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe wild read.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This approach preserves existing multi-handle teardown logic and only adjusts [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe cleanup sequence for DoH objects.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Other cleanup functions in the codebase [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., HTTP or SSL contexts[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m follow a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msimilar pattern of nullifying pointers post-free; this patch aligns [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_cleanup` with that practice.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects & Mitigations[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No impact on functionality: once the DoH context is cleaned up, further [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcleanup or teardown calls simply become no-ops.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes to public APIs or behavior of successful DoH queries.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing tests and fuzzing harness logic remain valid, as we only alter [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minternal cleanup behavior.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. References[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar cleanup patterns in `lib/http.c` and `lib/ftp.c` where pointers are [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mset to NULL after freeing.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensures consistency in resource management across the codebase.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         INFO: Running with entropic power schedule [1m([0m[1;36m0xFF[0m, [1;36m100[0m[1m)[0m.                              [2m               [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer run of `curl_fuzzer_http` on a minimal input triggered a SEGV in [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min lib/doh.c, line [0m[1;36m1410[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The user attempted a local patch in [0m    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A fuzz test invocation of `curl_fuzzer_http` with libFuzzer settings [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`-[0m[33mrss_limit_mb[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m2560[0m[39m -[0m[33mtimeout[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m25[0m[39m -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m loads a single testcase and crashes on[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe first input.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer reports a SEGV [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwild pointer read[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m inside `Curl_doh_close` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mdoh.[0m[1;92mc:1410[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The crash backtrace shows:  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * `Curl_doh_close` → `Curl_req_done` → `multi_done` → `multi_runsingle` → [0m     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No further ASan diagnostics are provided beyond the fact that a high-address [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdereference occurred.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Important Observations  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash happens during cleanup of a DOH [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDNS-over-HTTPS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m transaction, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msuggesting a freed or uninitialized pointer is being accessed.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The high-level fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcalling `curl_fuzzer_http`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is not at fault; it[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msimply drives the library through its API.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguarded by `#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH`.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Original snippet [0m[1;39m([0m[39mapproximate context[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The intent was to use the local `doh` variable for nulling fields and to also [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnull the pointer in `data->req.doh`, but the brace adjustments were misplaced.[0m      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This indicates the `[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` block’s braces no longer match: an extra or[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mplacement prevent the parser from recognizing the end of the `if` scope before the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`#endif`.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m94[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m95[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* The expected output length is [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes more than the length of[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m96[0m[39m:   * the QNAME-encoding of the hostname.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m97[0m[39m:   *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m98[0m[39m:   * A valid DNS name may not contain a zero-length label, except at[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m99[0m[39m:   * the end. For this reason, a name beginning with a dot, or[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100[0m[39m:   * containing a sequence of two or more consecutive dots, is invalid[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m101[0m[39m:   * and cannot be encoded as a QNAME.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m102[0m[39m:   *[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m103[0m[39m:   * If the hostname ends with a trailing dot, the corresponding[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m104[0m[39m:   * QNAME-encoding is one byte longer than the hostname. If [0m[1;39m([0m[39mas is[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m105[0m[39m:   * also valid[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m the hostname is shortened by the omission of the[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m106[0m[39m:   * trailing dot, then its QNAME-encoding will be two bytes longer[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m107[0m[39m:   * than the hostname.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m108[0m[39m:   *[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m109[0m[39m:   * Each [0m[1;39m[[0m[39m label, dot [0m[1;39m][0m[39m pair is encoded as [0m[1;39m[[0m[39m length, label [0m[1;39m][0m[39m,[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m110[0m[39m:   * preserving overall length. A final [0m[1;39m[[0m[39m label [0m[1;39m][0m[39m without a dot is[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m111[0m[39m:   * also encoded as [0m[1;39m[[0m[39m length, label [0m[1;39m][0m[39m, increasing overall length[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m112[0m[39m:   * by one. The encoding is completed by appending a zero byte,[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m113[0m[39m:   * representing the zero-length root label, again increasing[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m114[0m[39m:   * the overall length by one.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m115[0m[39m:   *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m116[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m117[0m[39m:  size_t expected_len;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m118[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mDEBUGASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mhostlen[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m119[0m[39m:  expected_len = [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m + hostlen + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m143[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mwhile[0m[1;39m([0m[39m*hostp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m147[0m[39m:      labellen = dot - hostp;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m149[0m[39m:      labellen = [0m[1;35mstrlen[0m[1;39m([0m[39mhostp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m150[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mlabellen > [0m[1;36m63[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!labellen[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m151[0m[39m:      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* label is too long or too short, error out *[0m[35m/[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m152[0m[39m:      *olen = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m153[0m[39m:      return DOH_DNS_BAD_LABEL;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m154[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m155[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* label is non-empty, process it *[0m[35m/[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m156[0m[39m:    *dnsp++ = [0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned char[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mlabellen;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m157[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdnsp, hostp, labellen[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m158[0m[39m:    dnsp += labellen;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m159[0m[39m:    hostp += labellen;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m160[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* advance past dot, but only if there is one *[0m[35m/[0m                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m162[0m[39m:      hostp++;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m163[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[39m* next label *[0m[35m/[0m                                                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m172[0m[39m:  *dnsp++ = DNS_CLASS_IN; [0m[35m/[0m[39m* IN - [0m[32m"the Internet"[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m175[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m176[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* verify that our estimation of length is valid, since[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m177[0m[39m:   * this has led to buffer overflows in this function *[0m[35m/[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m178[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mDEBUGASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39m*olen == expected_len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m182[0m[39m:static size_t[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m183:d[0m[1;35moh_write_cb[0m[1;39m([0m[39mchar *contents, size_t size, size_t nmemb, void *userp[0m[1;39m)[0m            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1434[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1435[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1436[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mcurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1437[0m[39m:    data->req.doh->req_hds = NULL;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1438[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1439[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1440[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Restore balanced braces in Curl_doh_cleanup:[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Open `lib/doh.c` and locate the function `Curl_doh_cleanup` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1431[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure the `[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` and its corresponding `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` are the only braces within [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat function, preserving the `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m1439[0m[39m and the function’s closing `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` at [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m1440[0m[39m. Remove any extra or misplaced braces introduced by the last patch.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Correct the cleanup sequence inside the `[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` block:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replace the erroneous references to `data->req.doh->req_hds` with the local [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`doh` pointer.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Free the header list, then clear the pointer in the struct before freeing the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstruct itself.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Leverage `[0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to free and null the `data->req.doh` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer in one step.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The resulting block should be:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mcurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       doh->req_hds = NULL;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This sequence ensures:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `Curl_doh_close` runs first, cleaning internal state.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `req_hds` is freed exactly once and its pointer cleared in the struct [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mavoiding stale reads in subsequent code[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • The DOH struct is freed and `data->req.doh` is set to NULL.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Do not add or remove any additional braces or touch any harness/fuzzing code:[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Only modify lines inside `Curl_doh_cleanup`.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Do not alter `#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH` [0m[35m/[0m[39m `#endif` boundaries or any other [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctions.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Leave all test and harness code unchanged so existing tests and fuzz targets [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinue to build and run identically.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Verify and test:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rebuild the library to confirm no brace mismatch or compiler errors remain.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run unit tests and the `curl_fuzzer_http` fuzz target to confirm that the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moriginal SEGV in `Curl_doh_close` no longer occurs [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor, if it still does, further [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstrumentation of `Curl_doh_close` may be needed[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Review AddressSanitizer logs to ensure no new use-after-free or double-free [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39missues are introduced.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This fix preserves the original intent of `Curl_doh_cleanup` while removing the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwild pointer dereference caused by nulling `data->req.doh->req_hds` after freeing [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe struct.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- By clearing `doh->req_hds` before freeing, we avoid any stale field inside the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstruct, and by using `Curl_safefree`, we both free and nullify `data->req.doh` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39matomically.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Keeping the brace structure minimal avoids mismatches with the encompassing [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`#ifdef` guard and ensures the function compiles cleanly.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All other logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnotably inside `Curl_doh_close`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is preserved, and no broad [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexception or harness modifications are introduced.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Similar cleanup patterns in other parts of libcurl [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., in the HTTP and FTP [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcleanup routines[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m follow this ordering and brace discipline, confirming consistency[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith the existing codebase.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m434[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m435[0m[39m:  conn->bits.doh = TRUE;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m436[0m[39m:  dohp->host = hostname;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m437[0m[39m:  dohp->port = port;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m438[0m[39m:  dohp->req_hds =[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m439[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mcurl_slist_append[0m[1;39m([0m[39mNULL,[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m440[0m[39m:                      [0m[32m"Content-Type: application/dns-message"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m441[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!dohp->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m442[0m[39m:    goto error;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m443[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m444[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* create IPv4 DoH request *[0m[35m/[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m445[0m[39m:  result = [0m[1;35mdoh_run_probe[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, &dohp->probe[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mDOH_SLOT_IPV4[0m[1;39m][0m[39m,[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m446[0m[39m:                         DNS_TYPE_A, hostname, data->set.str[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mSTRING_DOH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m,[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m447[0m[39m:                         data->multi, dohp->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m448[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mresult[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m449[0m[39m:    goto error;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m450[0m[39m:  dohp->pending++;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1431[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1440[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1431[0m[39m:void [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1432[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1433[0m[39m:  struct doh_probes *doh = data->req.doh;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1434[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1435[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1436[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mcurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1437[0m[39m:    data->req.doh->req_hds = NULL;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1438[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1439[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1440[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/request.[0m[1;92mc:105[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m112[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m105[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvoid[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35mreq_flush[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m106[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_client_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m107[0m[39m:#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m108[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m109[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m110[0m[39m:  return CURLE_OK;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m111[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m112[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The AddressSanitizer crash in Curl_doh_close stems from a dangling pointer: [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafter the DoH resources are freed by Curl_doh_cleanup, `data->req.doh` is not reset[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto NULL. A later call to Curl_doh_close [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfrom Curl_req_done[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m sees a non‐NULL [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh`, binds it into a local `doh` pointer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpointing at already‐freed [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemory[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and reads fields from it, causing a wild read.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The last patch only corrected the null‐assignment of the header list [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`req_hds`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to use the local `doh` pointer but did not prevent the dangling pointer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto the `doh_probes` struct itself.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Critical Logic to Preserve[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Curl_doh_close must continue to close any outstanding DoH sub-handles without [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfreeing the `doh_probes` struct itself.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Curl_doh_cleanup retains responsibility for freeing the HTTP header list and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `doh_probes` allocation.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The existing fuzzer harness and multi/transfer cleanup flow must remain [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munchanged; we must not alter harness logic or remove functionality.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Proposed Patch Steps[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. In lib/doh.c, extend Curl_doh_cleanup to nullify the pointer to the freed [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructure:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      void [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        struct doh_probes *doh = data->req.doh;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mcurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          doh->req_hds = NULL;                  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m keep local pointer clear[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;         [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m frees doh_probes memory[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          data->req.doh = NULL;                 [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m <--- NEW: prevent dangling [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. [0m[1;39m([0m[39mAlready applied[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Use `doh->req_hds = NULL` instead of [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh->req_hds = NULL` to avoid dereferencing freed `data->req.doh` during[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcleanup.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. No changes to Curl_req_done [0m[1;39m([0m[39mstill calls Curl_doh_close only[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m so that the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mper-transfer “close‐only” cleanup remains separate from the full struct teardown [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdone by Curl_doh_cleanup.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   D. Ensure that Curl_doh_cleanup is invoked exactly once per completed [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrequest/connection teardown so that `data->req.doh` is cleared before any later [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCurl_doh_close.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By nullifying `data->req.doh` immediately after freeing the structure, any [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubsequent call to Curl_doh_close will see `data->req.doh == NULL` and exit early, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mavoiding the wild dereference.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This patch is minimal, preserves the existing division of responsibilities [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbetween Curl_doh_close [0m[1;39m([0m[39msub‐handle closing[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and Curl_doh_cleanup [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfull teardown[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand does not touch harness code, fuzzing logic, or external libraries.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It directly addresses the root cause [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdangling pointer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, eliminates the wild [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mread, and retains all legitimate DoH teardown semantics.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar cleanup idioms in the codebase [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., other protocol cleanup functions[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mset their pointer to NULL after free[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m confirm this is the approved pattern.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Side-Effect Mitigation[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No functional behavior is changed in normal “close‐only” paths. Full DoH [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mteardown still frees headers and the struct.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Nullifying the pointer cannot hide any real error; the only change is [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreventing use-after-free in the rare case of a stray Curl_doh_close after cleanup.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing tests and the fuzzer harness should pass, since the DoH cleanup still[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhappens exactly once and no new error paths are introduced.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer crash was detected when running the `curl_fuzzer_http` fuzzer [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39magainst a crafted input. The failure originates in `Curl_doh_close` within [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`lib/doh.c`, showing a wild-memory read dereference. A patch was attempted that [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madjusted pointer resets and frees in `lib/doh.c`—specifically nulling [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`doh->req_hds` and zeroing `data->req.doh` after freeing—but the segmentation fault[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `Curl_doh_close` persisted in an identical location.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer log reports a SEGV in `Curl_doh_close` at lib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1410[0m[39m.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This is triggered by a READ from an invalid [0m[1;39m([0m[39mhigh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m address, indicating a wild [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer or use-after-free.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack trace shows `Curl_req_done` → `multi_done` → `curl_multi_perform` → [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`fuzz_handle_transfer` → `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No additional AddressSanitizer details beyond “wild-addr-read” were emitted.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant Observations  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash consistently occurs inside `Curl_doh_close`.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The input is processed via libcurl’s DNS-over-HTTPS [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDOH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m path.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The invalid read happens before any visible user code, indicating an internal [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcleanup or state corruption.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After failure, the fuzzer run is aborted with exit status [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `lib/doh.c`, at around line [0m[1;36m1434[0m[39m, the patch:[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Calls `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` only if `doh` is non-NULL.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Frees the header list with `[0m[1;35mcurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Replaces `data->req.doh->req_hds = NULL;` with `doh->req_hds = NULL;`.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Calls `[0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` then sets `data->req.doh = NULL;`.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The intent was to avoid dangling pointers and clear the DOH request structure.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After rebuilding with the patch, the fuzzer reproduces the crash at the same code[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocation in `Curl_doh_close`.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack trace and sanitizer output remain effectively unchanged, indicating the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch did not prevent the wild-memory read.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The implementation of `Curl_doh_close` around line [0m[1;36m1410[0m[39m in `lib/doh.c`: verify [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich internal pointers it dereferences and their lifetimes.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The allocation and ownership of `data->req.doh` and related members [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`req_hds`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Interaction between `Curl_req_done` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `lib/request.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and DOH cleanup [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctions.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Multi-handle cleanup functions [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`multi_done`, `multi_runsingle`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to see if [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close` is invoked redundantly or with stale state.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer entry point [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fuzz_handle_transfer` in `curl_fuzzer.cc`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to confirm [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlifecycle expectations for DOH objects before and after the transfer.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m199[0m[39m:    char *p = [0m[1;35mgetenv[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"CURL_SMALLREQSEND"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m200[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1385[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1395[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1385[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mdoh_print_httpsrr[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, hrr[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
