[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1388[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1389[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1390[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1391[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* All done *[0m[35m/[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1392[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mde_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1393[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1394[0m[39m:    return result;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1395[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/request.[0m[1;92mc:103[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m110[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m103[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvoid[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mreq;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m104[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!aborted[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m105[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvoid[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35mreq_flush[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m106[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_client_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m107[0m[39m:#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m108[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m109[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m110[0m[39m:  return CURLE_OK;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Identify root cause[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The function Curl_doh [0m[1;39m([0m[39min lib/doh.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m performs an early cleanup of the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh` struct after DNS-over-HTTPS resolution completes:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mde_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;    ← frees and nulls `data->req.doh`[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        return result;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Later, when the request finishes, `Curl_req_done` unconditionally calls [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. Because `data->req.doh` has already been freed [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand in some[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode paths may still be a dangling pointer if not yet nulled[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, `Curl_doh_close` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdereferences invalid memory [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doh->probe[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.easy_mid`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and crashes.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Preserve critical logic[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We must still free the header list [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doh->req_hds`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m after resolution to avoid [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemory leaks.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We must continue to handle outstanding DOH probe transfers [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m at request teardown.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `doh_probes` struct itself must persist from the first DNS-over-HTTPS [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlookup until the request is completely done.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch approach[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. In lib/doh.c, inside the main DNS-over-HTTPS function [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m1391[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreplace the premature call to `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with a minimal [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“resolution-only” cleanup:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Free the header list: `[0m[1;35mcurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Reset `doh->req_hds = NULL`[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - **Do not** call `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or free the `data->req.doh` struct [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhere.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Return `result`.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Leave `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` unchanged. It will be called later from:[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - `Curl_req_done` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min lib/request.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - `Curl_req_free` [0m[35m/[0m[39m `Curl_req_hard_reset`[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     This ensures the DOH probe struct is only freed when the request is truly [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomplete.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Detailed steps[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m In lib/doh.c, locate the block:[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* All done *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mde_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      return result;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Change it to:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* All done: free only headers, keep doh_probes alive until request-end *[0m[35m/[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mde_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mcurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        data->req.doh->req_hds = NULL;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      return result;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Ensure that `data->req.doh` remains non-NULL so that the later call in [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_req_done`:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #endif[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      correctly iterates existing probe slots [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich by then should all be [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`easy_mid = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m without crashing, and that `Curl_doh_cleanup` will finally free [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh`.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By removing the early free of the `doh_probes` struct, we avoid the [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muse-after-free in `Curl_doh_close` at request teardown.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We still free the per-resolution resources [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`req_hds`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m immediately to prevent [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mleaks.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We defer freeing the full DOH state until the standard cleanup path in [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_req_done` or `Curl_req_free`, preserving the intended lifecycle.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This change is internal to libcurl’s DOH implementation; it does not touch [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz harness code, external libraries, or tests.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Potential side effects and mitigation[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The DOH struct lives slightly longer [0m[1;39m([0m[39muntil request-end[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but since it is [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfreed exactly once by `Curl_doh_cleanup`, no additional memory leak occurs.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `Curl_doh_close` may run on a struct with all probe slots already `[0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moperations[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which is safe.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing tests and functionality remain unchanged: header lists are freed, no [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdouble-free happens, and request-level cleanup still removes any multi handles.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Reference to similar patterns[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - libcurl often separates “per-operation” cleanup and “per-request” cleanup [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39me.g., `Curl_client_cleanup` vs. `Curl_client_reset`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Here, we introduce a similar[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msplit within the DOH code.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo additional file retrieval is required.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer run of the `curl_fuzzer_http` target consistently crashes with an [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer SEGV in `Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlib/doh.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m due to a wild memory read. An[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempted patch modifies `lib/doh.c` around the cleanup paths: it replaces a call [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` after `[0m[1;35mde_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with manual freeing of [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh->req_hds` and nulling that pointer, and in the separate close path [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmoves and extends the header free/null logic alongside nulling `data->req.doh`. [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying this patch, the same SEGV in `Curl_doh_close` is still reproducible,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malbeit at a slightly shifted source line.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Invoking `curl_fuzzer_http` under libFuzzer with a supplied testcase triggers [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma segmentation fault in `Curl_doh_close` at `lib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1410:30[0m[39m`.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer run log shows:  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     …[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer marks it as a “wild-addr-read” from a high-value address, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating use-after-free or uninitialized pointer.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash stack always enters `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` from `Curl_req_done`, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msuggesting the DOH [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDNS-over-HTTPS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m cleanup path is not handling its internal [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointers correctly.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Observations in the Initial Issue  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The function `Curl_doh_close` is called unconditionally when `data->req.doh` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis non-NULL.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch log indicates that after `de_cleanup`, the original code called [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` which likely frees or nulls internal `data->req.doh`, but [0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash always reproduces in the same code path of DOH teardown.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash originates from an uncleaned or partially initialized [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh` context leaking into the request teardown. In particular, inside [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_is_resolved[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, the branch handling HTTPS RR decode failures [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`doh_resp_decode_httpsrr`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m returns early without invoking the normal cleanup [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msequence [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mde_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. As a result, [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh` remains allocated with its `probe` slots either zeroed [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfrom [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`calloc`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or later partially set [0m[1;39m([0m[39mheader list non-NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but the `easy_mid` slots [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnever get recognized as [0m[32m"done"[0m[39m, leading to wild reads in `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All other late cleanup attempts [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe manual header freeing patch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m did not [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevent `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` from iterating these stale slots.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Principles to Preserve[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Maintain the existing DOH happy-path cleanup sequence: always call [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mde_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` then `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` before any return from the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresolution routines.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure that after `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns, `data->req.doh` is NULL [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand no probe handles remain outstanding.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Do not alter fuzzer harness or test code; only modify `lib/doh.c`.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep the two-stage cleanup:  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Per-DNS-packet parsing free via `[0m[1;35mde_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Global DOH context teardown via `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Implementation Steps[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Locate the `doh_resp_decode_httpsrr` failure path in `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_is_resolved[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39maround lines [0m[1;36m1375[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m1382[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Prepend the standard cleanup calls before the early `return result;`, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmirroring the normal exit at lines [0m[1;36m1391[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m1394[0m[39m:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mresult[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35minfof[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Failed to decode HTTPS RR"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mde_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        return result;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Search for any other `goto error;` or `return` statements in [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_is_resolved[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or related DOH routines that bypass the [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call. For each, insert the same two cleanup calls before [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturning.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Double-check that `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` consistently sets `data->req.doh = [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNULL` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mit must to avoid subsequent `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` from seeing a non-NULL [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontext[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. If it doesn’t already, augment it to nullify `data->req.doh` at its end.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Rebuild and rerun the fuzzer to ensure the wild-read SEGV in [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` no longer occurs. Confirm that on HTTPS RR decode failures the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcleanup correctly deallocates the probes and context, leaving no residual [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`easy_mid` slots.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Why This Fix[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It directly addresses the missing cleanup path identified in the analysis. By [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmirroring the successful-path cleanup before any early return, we guarantee that no[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstale DOH context remains.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It preserves the existing logic and lifecycle model of DOH requests, only [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextending cleanup coverage.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It avoids touching harness, fuzzing logic, or external dependencies.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects and Mitigations[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Side Effect**: If other error branches exist and have not been similarly [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfixed, those too must be audited.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     **Mitigation**: Perform a grep for `return` or `goto error` in `lib/doh.c` and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensure each path cleans up.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Side Effect**: Double-free risk if `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is modified [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincorrectly.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     **Mitigation**: Rely on existing tests; confirm no new failures appear in the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munit test suite.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Side Effect**: If `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` does not nullify `data->req.doh`, a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubsequent `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` might still see an invalid pointer.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     **Mitigation**: Explicitly set `data->req.doh = NULL` at the end of [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` if not already done.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Verification[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm that in AddressSanitizer logs, no wild-address reads occur in [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run the full FAKE or regression test suite for DoH to verify no breakage in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnormal DNS-over-HTTPS flows.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validate memory leaks with ASan LeakSanitizer that no DOH context remains [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafter error paths.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo external files or harness modifications are required. This targeted cleanup [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minsertion resolves the segmentation fault while preserving all existing [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctionality.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
